                <note rend="inline" type="source">863.51 Relief Credits/237: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-05-29T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 29, 1930—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>43. Your 37, May 26, noon. What is the meaning of the phrase “the release of
                    these guarantees is subject to the Hague agreements,” particularly as the Hague
                    agreements are understood to have come into force before date of Italian
                    statement?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
